<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">
The aedeagus of the two genera are similar in shape, but it is slightly longer and straight, and the carina process is more pointed in the new genus than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1973" box="[592,702,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Marplena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[592,702,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Marplena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the vesica of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="László" authorityYear="2022" box="[1021,1191,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Watsonopsestis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1021,1191,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Watsonopsestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a well-developed diverticulum medially, which is absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1973" box="[620,730,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Marplena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[620,730,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Marplena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">
In the female genitalia, the main differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1973" box="[841,951,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Marplena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,951,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Marplena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="László" authorityYear="2022" box="[1017,1187,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Watsonopsestis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1017,1187,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Watsonopsestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are expressed in the considerably narrower ostium bursae and the markedly larger, elongate signum bursae compared to the small, round signum of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lane" authorityYear="1973" box="[271,381,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Marplena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[271,381,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="363">Marplena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
